### List all guests
GET http://localhost:8080/api/guests

### Create guest (groom side)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/guests
Content-Type: application/json
user-racf: myuser

{
  "first_name": "João",
  "last_name": "Silva",
  "phone": "11999999999",
  "relationship": "groom"
}

### Create guest (bride side)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/guests
Content-Type: application/json
user-racf: myuser

{
  "first_name": "Maria",
  "last_name": "Santos",
  "phone": "11888888888",
  "relationship": "bride"
}

### Get guest by ID (replace with a real ID from the list response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/guests/REPLACE-WITH-UUID

### Update guest — confirm attendance
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/guests/REPLACE-WITH-UUID
Content-Type: application/json
user-racf: myuser

{
  "confirmed": true
}

### Update guest — change phone
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/guests/REPLACE-WITH-UUID
Content-Type: application/json
user-racf: myuser

{
  "phone": "11777777777"
}

### Delete guest
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/guests/REPLACE-WITH-UUID
user-racf: myuser

### Import CSV
POST http://localhost:8080/api/guests/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary
user-racf: PAMC7

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="guests.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

first_name,last_name,phone,relationship
